Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, low CO₂, and mild ALT elevation, suggesting possible renal impairment with mild metabolic acidosis and some hepatic involvement. Urinalysis reveals significant proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria, with low specific gravity and abnormal appearance, indicating possible nephrotic syndrome or diabetic nephropathy. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend further evaluation of renal and hepatic function and assessment for diabetes mellitus.
